1. Go to Oracle and Install JDK1.8 - https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/javase/javase-jdk8-downloads.html
2. Once installed, go to system  environment variable
3. Get path of JDK 1.8 eg. C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.8.0_261 - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=104dNWmM6Rs&ab_channel=CodeJava
4. Set under system variable not! variable for %userprofile% JAVA_HOME TO C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.8.0_261
5. Under PATH add also %JAVA_HOME%/bin
6. Open cmd and run java -version and javac -version to ensure everything is working correctly
